OL,3,CThree-week delay in finding soldier's
OL,4,Cbody in barracks 'unforgivable'
OL,6,FAn inquest, held at North Yorkshire
OL,7,FCoroners' Court in Northallerton,
OL,8,Fheard L/Cpl Mongan had "obviously been
OL,9,Fdead for some time" when he was found,
OL,10,Fand had last been seen around 27
OL,11,FDecember.
OL,13,FDoctors were unable to determine a
OL,14,Fcause of death because of the
OL,15,Fcondition of his body.
OL,17,FThe hearing, which started on 2 June,
OL,18,Fwas told of claims L/Cpl Mongan was
OL,19,Fbullied by senior officers and that
OL,20,Fthe family believed he had taken his
OL,21,Fown life.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/11
