OL,3,CThree-week delay in finding soldier's
OL,4,Cbody in barracks 'unforgivable'
OL,6,FSpeaking outside court after the
OL,7,Fverdict, Mrs Mongan said she was
OL,8,Fexpecting the open conclusion "mainly
OL,9,Fdue to the army's failure of leaving
OL,10,F(L/Cpl Mongan) for so long".
OL,12,FShe said: "I've come to my own
OL,13,Fconclusions over the years, it's hard
OL,14,Fnot having it for the kids.
OL,16,F"It's been a rollercoaster.
OL,18,F"He was funny, he would try to make
OL,19,Fanybody joke, anybody laugh, he had a
OL,20,Frather weird but wicked sense of
OL,21,Fhumour. He was an amazing dad."
