OL,3,CThree-week delay in finding soldier's
OL,4,Cbody in barracks 'unforgivable'
OL,6,F"However, his wife Beth has been in
OL,7,Fcourt every single day and has heard
OL,8,Fand read all of the evidence for
OL,9,Fherself, and the coroner did find
OL,10,Ftoday that Bernie was subjected to
OL,11,Ftreatment and was spoken to in a
OL,12,Fmanner by his chain of command that
OL,13,Fcaused him distress.
OL,15,F"The other word for that in his wife's
OL,16,Fopinion is bullying."
OL,18,FShe added: "It remains the view of his
OL,19,Fwife that Bernie died by his own hand
OL,20,Fand that he was in lots of ways very
OL,21,Fbadly let down by the army."
